# BookExchange Project Structure

This is a full-stack book exchange social network with the following structure:

## Main Directories
- [backend/](mdc:backend/) - Django-Ninja API server with PostgreSQL
- [frontend/](mdc:frontend/) - React TypeScript application with Material-UI
- [infra/](mdc:infra/) - Terraform infrastructure for Google Cloud deployment
- [.github/workflows/](mdc:.github/workflows/) - GitHub Actions CI/CD pipelines

## Key Configuration Files
- [docker-compose.yml](mdc:docker-compose.yml) - Local development environment
- [README.md](mdc:README.md) - Project documentation and setup instructions
- [.gitignore](mdc:.gitignore) - Git ignore patterns for all stack components

## Backend Structure
- [backend/bookexchange/settings.py](mdc:backend/bookexchange/settings.py) - Django configuration
- [backend/bookexchange/urls.py](mdc:backend/bookexchange/urls.py) - Main URL routing with Django-Ninja API
- [backend/requirements.txt](mdc:backend/requirements.txt) - Python dependencies
- [backend/Dockerfile](mdc:backend/Dockerfile) - Production Docker container
- [backend/env.template](mdc:backend/env.template) - Environment variables template

## Frontend Structure
- [frontend/package.json](mdc:frontend/package.json) - Node.js dependencies and scripts
- [frontend/Dockerfile](mdc:frontend/Dockerfile) - Production Docker container
- [frontend/nginx.conf](mdc:frontend/nginx.conf) - Nginx configuration for serving React app

## Infrastructure
- [infra/main.tf](mdc:infra/main.tf) - Main Terraform configuration
- [infra/variables.tf](mdc:infra/variables.tf) - Terraform input variables
- [infra/outputs.tf](mdc:infra/outputs.tf) - Terraform outputs
- [infra/terraform.tfvars.example](mdc:infra/terraform.tfvars.example) - Example variables file

## Django Apps
Each Django app follows the standard structure with models, views (API), and migrations:
- `accounts/` - User management and authentication
- `books/` - Book catalog and user collections
- `friendships/` - Social connections and friend requests
- `exchanges/` - Book exchange system
- `messaging/` - Private messages and public discussions
